casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Walton, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Walton (1996), 77 Ohio St.3d 1205.]

(No. 95-2262 Submitted October 9, 1996 Decided November 6, 1996.) Russell B. Wiseman, Crawford County Prosecuting Attorney, and Lee A. Oldendick, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. Frederick Walton, pro se.

The appeal is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Stratton, JJ., concur.
